GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 27th November, 2004
6 Agrahayana, 1926(S).
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 27th November,
2004 -
The Prime Minister relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
Coal and Mines;
i)
ii)
Shri Shibu Soren assumed the charge of the office of Minister of Coal;
Shri Sis Ram Ola relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
Labour & Employment and assumed the charge of the office of Minister
of Mines;
iii)
Shri K. Chandra Sekhar Rao relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister without Portfolio and assumed the charge of the office of
Minister of Labour & Employment; and
iv)
Dr. Dasari Narayan Rao relinquished the charge of the office of Minister
of State in the Ministry of Coal & Mines and assumed the charge of the
office of Minister of State in the Ministry of Coal and the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Mines.
Qu
